Changes from 2.0.3 to 2.0.4 - released 2010/xx/yy

*General:
- cluster support is fully functional again: ezdfs setups are now possible
- added update script up to eZ Publish version 4.3.0 final
- added update script up to eZ Publish version 4.4.0beta1
- added update script up to eZ Publish versions 4.1.5, 4.2.1 and 4.3.1 (all of them unreleased)

*Bugfixes:
- improved 4.0 to 4.1 update scripts for the case where ezgeneral_digest_user_settings table has rows with NULL address
- fixed the generated sql for correcting database schema when a varchar column is being migrated to clob (in the 'Setup|Upgrade check' page)
- fixed bug: eznumvalue table columns should be nullable, or it is impossible to add enum attributes to classes (even though it's a deprecated datatype)
- fixed bug: script ora-drop-schema.php has a bug preventing proper dropping of functions
- fixed bug #017017: Errors in Migration/Update Script
- fixed bug #017183: fetchExpiredBinaryItems function missing from oracle ezdb cluster handler
- fixed bug #017184: oracle ezdb cluster handler: zero byte files not supported

*Enhancements:
- Implemented enhancement #017157: optimize memory usage of index_image_mysql for big images
- Implemented enhancement #017158: Allow persistent database connections in index_image.php and friends
- Implemented enhancement #017159: Allow index_image_mysql.php (and others) to honour Etag http headers
- Implemented enhancement #017160: Allow index_image_mysql.php (and others) to play nice with keepalive
- Implemented enhancement #016513: Add ability to define Expires offset send by index_cluster.php
- renamed the accumulator used for select queries to make it more uniform with mysql/postgres
